---
layout: layout-base.njk
title: Garden Planning Guides | Frost Dates, Seed Starting & Crop Timing | GrowByDate
description: Practical gardening guides for frost dates, seed starting, transplant timing, crop maturity, and short-season planning.
canonical: "https://growbydate.com/guides/"
---

{% macro guideLinkBySlug(slug) %}
  {% for p in collections.guides | sort(attribute="data.title") %}
    {% if p.fileSlug == slug %}
      {% set rawTitle = p.data.title or p.fileSlug %}
      {% set cleanTitle = rawTitle | replace(" | GrowByDate", "") %}
      <li class="index-item">
        <a class="index-link" href="{{ p.url }}"><strong>{{ cleanTitle }}</strong></a>
        {% if p.data.description %}
          <div class="small index-desc">{{ p.data.description }}</div>
        {% endif %}
      </li>
    {% endif %}
  {% endfor %}
{% endmacro %}

<section class="card leaderboardHero">
  <p class="eyebrow">Garden planning guides</p>
  <h1>Garden Planning Guides for Short Seasons</h1>

  <p class="lede">
    Use these guides to plan around frost dates, limited heat, seed-starting windows, transplant timing, and crop maturity risk.
    They are organized by the actual planning problem, not as one long alphabetical archive.
  </p>

  <p>
    Short-season gardening is not just about counting calendar days. Frost dates define the outside edge of the season, while growing degree days show how much useful warmth crops usually receive inside that window.
    Start with the first section if you are new, or jump to the topic that matches the decision you are working on.
  </p>
</section>

{% for section in guideHub %}
  <section class="card index-card">
    <h2>{{ section.title }}</h2>

    {% if section.description %}
      <p class="small intro">{{ section.description }}</p>
    {% endif %}

    <ul class="index-list">
      {% for slug in section.slugs %}
        {{ guideLinkBySlug(slug) }}
      {% endfor %}
    </ul>
  </section>
{% endfor %}
